                            <comment id="13836502" author="anoop.hbase" created="Mon, 2 Dec 2013 13:24:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Creating Scan in CP?  Can you tell us more regarding ur usage context pls?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13836532" author="vikramsinghchandel" created="Mon, 2 Dec 2013 14:09:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;our normal scan are taking around 62 seconds for around 8.1 million records. And anything beyond 5 sec is not acceptable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13837227" author="vasu.mariyala@gmail.com" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 01:52:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only when the filter columns are part of the scan column list, the filter is applied. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4364&quot; title=&quot;Filters applied to columns not in the selected column list are ignored&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4364&quot;&gt;HBASE-4364&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14044578" author="vikramsinghchandel" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 11:21:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any solution available for this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14044649" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 13:25:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You have to add the condition column also on to the Scan and if that column value not needed use SingleColumnValueExcludeFilter instead of SCVF.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
